e there exist the [[{{ill|North River Upper Ruins|ja|北川表の上遺跡|12=draft|12=draft}}]] and [[{{ill|North River Shell Mound|ja|北川貝塚|12=draft|12=draft}}]], and the ''Newly Compiled Musashi Fudoki Manuscript, Yoshida Village'' records that “a large shell mound existed in Yoshida Village of Tsuzuki District” {{sfn|Newly Compiled Musashi Fudoki Manuscript, Yoshida Village}}, with the local name “Shell Mound Field” still in use – evidence that archaeological sites in the area have long been known.<ref name="tsugaruoukoku-sugiyama"/> 

Like many other ronsya, the shrine is situated on an elevated spot along the {{ill|Tsurumi River|ja|鶴見川|12=draft|12=draft}} of the {{ill|water system|ja|水系|12=draft|12=draft}} ({{ill|Hayabuchi River|ja|早渕川|12=draft|12=draft}}).

